history.content: If you can find a lecture-lab-discussion combo, each having open seats, you should be enrolled in the class during the next processing event (happens at least once a day). You can also use the swap feature if there is a certain section that you absolutely want.

It does like there should be seats open for which you qualify if you are an EECS major. The answer above is mostly correct. As long as you are wait listed for a section, the system will keep you on the wait list for the lecture even if there are open seats for the lecture.

If you are currently on the wait list, you will need to drop the class, select sections that have open seats and re-enroll. The swap feature only works if you are already enrolled in the class and want to change sections. 

And right now the system is processing enrollments 4 times a day so you may have to wait a few hours to see any change reflected.

I am an upcoming Sophomore in EECS, and I am trying to enroll into CS61C this Fall (phase 2). However, I see this on Calcentral. Does this mean I cannot enroll into the course? I am asking because if I want to phase 2 61C, I would need to drop one course (I have four courses right now). Hence, I don't want to risk dropping one of the courses and not get into 61C.

Any ideas?
